# GitHub Issue Template Setup Guide

## 📁 File Structure
Create this folder structure in your repository:

```
your-repo/
├── .github/
│   ├── ISSUE_TEMPLATE/
│   │   ├── config.yml
│   │   └── onboarding_request.yml
│   └── workflows/
│       └── onboarding_automation.yml
└── README.md
```

## 📝 Step-by-Step Setup

### 1. Create the Issue Template
Save the onboarding YAML form as:
`.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/onboarding_request.yml`

### 2. Configure Issue Template Chooser
Create `.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/config.yml`:

```yaml
blank_issues_enabled: false
contact_links:
  - name: 🆘 Platform Support
    url: https://your-company.slack.com/channels/platform-support
    about: For urgent platform issues or questions
  - name: 📖 Platform Documentation
    url: https://docs.your-platform.com
    about: Check our documentation for common questions
```

### 3. Create GitHub Actions Workflow (Optional)
Create `.github/workflows/onboarding_automation.yml`:

```yaml
name: Onboarding Request Automation

on:
  issues:
    types: [opened]

jobs:
  process_onboarding:
    if: contains(github.event.issue.labels.*.name, 'onboarding')
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    
    steps:
    - name: Auto-assign to Platform Team
      uses: actions/github-script@v6
      with:
        script: |
          github.rest.issues.addAssignees({
            owner: context.repo.owner,
            repo: context.repo.repo,
            issue_number: context.issue.number,
            assignees: ['platform-admin', 'devops-lead']
          });

    - name: Add to Platform Project
      uses: actions/github-script@v6
      with:
        script: |
          // Add to project board
          github.rest.projects.createCard({
            column_id: 12345, // Replace with your project column ID
            content_id: context.issue.number,
            content_type: 'Issue'
          });

    - name: Send Slack Notification
      uses: 8398a7/action-slack@v3
      with:
        status: custom
        custom_payload: |
          {
            text: "New onboarding request from ${{ github.event.issue.user.login }}",
            attachments: [{
              color: 'good',
              fields: [{
                title: 'Issue',
                value: '<${{ github.event.issue.html_url }}|${{ github.event.issue.title }}>',
                short: true
              }]
            }]
          }
      env:
        SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL: ${{ secrets.SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL }}
```

## 🔧 Advanced Configuration

### Custom Labels and Automation
Add these labels to your repository:
- `onboarding` (blue)
- `namespace-request` (yellow) 
- `capability-request` (purple)
- `urgent` (red)
- `approved` (green)
- `in-progress` (orange)

### Issue Templates Configuration
You can create multiple templates:

```yaml
# .github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/config.yml
blank_issues_enabled: false
contact_links:
  - name: 🚀 Onboarding Request
    url: https://github.com/yourorg/yourrepo/issues/new?template=onboarding_request.yml
    about: Request access to platform namespaces and capabilities
  - name: 🐛 Bug Report  
    url: https://github.com/yourorg/yourrepo/issues/new?template=bug_report.yml
    about: Report a platform issue
  - name: 💡 Feature Request
    url: https://github.com/yourorg/yourrepo/issues/new?template=feature_request.yml
    about: Suggest a new platform feature
```

## 📊 Analytics and Tracking

### Issue Templates with Better Analytics
Add these fields to track metrics:

```yaml
# Add to your onboarding_request.yml
- type: dropdown
  id: department
  attributes:
    label: Department
    options:
      - Engineering
      - Data Science
      - Product
      - Marketing
      - Operations
  validations:
    required: true

- type: dropdown
  id: team-size
  attributes:
    label: Team Size
    options:
      - "1-5 people"
      - "6-15 people" 
      - "16-50 people"
      - "50+ people"
```

## 🔐 Security Considerations

### Sensitive Information Handling
For sensitive requests, add:

```yaml
- type: checkboxes
  id: security-clearance
  attributes:
    label: Security Clearance
    options:
      - label: This request involves sensitive data
      - label: This request requires security review
      - label: This request involves external integrations
```

### Auto-redaction for Public Repos
If your repo is public, add a warning:

```yaml
- type: markdown
  attributes:
    value: |
      ⚠️ **Security Notice**: This repository is public. 
      Do not include sensitive information like passwords, API keys, or proprietary data.
```
